                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d560">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11 <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_EH1"
                        >Ekvall, Henry</persName>/2: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-04T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 4, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 4—2:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>898. Hankow’s August 3, noon, concerning disappearance of <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_EH1">Henry Ekvall</persName> an American citizen in
                    company with a Swede and a Japanese national last seen near Sianfu. Legation has
                    instructed Counselor <persName>Peck</persName> at Nanking to make urgent
                    representations in the matter to the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
